          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"key-insights\">Key Insights</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Czech Republic leads at 12.85 litres per capita, followed closely by France (12.6) and Ireland (12.51)</li>\n<li>Russia at 7.03L is lower than many Western European countries, reflecting anti-alcohol campaigns</li>\n<li>Muslim-majority countries (Iran, Pakistan, Indonesia) cluster near zero</li>\n<li>India reports just 0.002L per capita, likely reflecting underreporting and large abstinent populations</li>\n</ul></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
